CSS are of two types:-
~ INLINE CSS
~ INTERNAL CSS
~ EXTERNAL CSS

~INLINE CSS:-
# This is the type of style where you style the tag by writing the features as attributes in the tag itself.
# <section style="background-color: #fffff; color: #333; margin: 20px; padding: 20px; border: 2px;

~ INTERNAL CSS:-
# This is done by the help of <style> tag. The tag will be written within the <head> tag section. For example:-
<head>
 <style>
    body{
      color: #3fff;
      background-color:#ffffff;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 2px;
    }
</style>
# We assign each of like id and class for each tags and write the styling inside the style tag for the speicific ones.
# For id we can just write as follows: classname{} and for classnames we can write as follows: .classname{}
# id can be used when there is a need to select individually.
# class can be used when we'll have to style multiple elements with the same style.

~EXTERNAL CSS:-
# This type is done by creating another external file and writing the contents in them.
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./style.css">
# In external css, we can make use of the id's assigned for each tags.
